                <div class="article-content fs-5 text-dark-emphasis">
                    <p class="lead fw-normal">Blossom World Senior Secondary School celebrated Republic Day with great enthusiasm and patriotic spirit on the school grounds.</p>
                    
                    <p>The event began with the hoisting of the National Flag, followed by the National Anthem, instilling a deep sense of pride and respect among students and staff. Students from various classes participated in the programme, showcasing discipline, unity, and teamwork.</p>

                    <blockquote class="my-5 p-4 border-start border-5 border-orange bg-light rounded-end italic shadow-sm">
                        <p class="mb-0 fs-4">"Such occasions help students understand the significance of the Constitution and the responsibilities of being responsible citizens."</p>
                    </blockquote>

                    <p>Dressed in colourful uniforms and proudly carrying the school flag, the children reflected the values of national integrity and collective responsibility. Teachers and staff guided the students throughout the event, ensuring a well-organised and meaningful celebration.</p>
                    
                    <p>At Blossom World Senior Secondary School, national celebrations are an integral part of holistic education, encouraging students to develop respect for the nation, discipline in conduct, and confidence in leadership.</p>
